Steve Doctrow has an established name in the international marketing, publicity and promotional disciplines. With unbridled creativity, professionalism, strategic knowhow and an entrepreneurial drive, Doctrow has amassed more than 25 years of experience. He currently holds the title of Executive Vice President of Entertainment Marketing for the internationally-recognized firm Rogers & Cowan. Doctrow has fostered integrated marketing campaigns for an array of clients in the corporate and entertainment markets. Doctrow has also been the recipient of multiple PRISM Awards from the Public Relations Society of America. 
Doctrow is a central part of Rogers & Cowan's growing presence in China and the Pacific Rim. With a team of global professionals, and brand supported media events, Doctrow has grown business relationships in the region and expanded opportunities.
Doctrow was the Senior Vice President at Premiere Radio Networks before his time with Rogers & Cowan. At Premiere Radio Networks, Doctrow oversaw numerous promotional marketing campaigns for Fortune 500 companies, with a special focus on consumer electronics, entertainment and the packaged goods industries. 
Doctrow has overseen worldwide public relations campaigns, from securing global talent for The Venetian Macau to staging media and celebrity events in Australia, Beijing, Brazil, Germany, Shanghai, Switzerland, Taipei, Tokyo, Toronto and the United Kingdom.
Earlier on in his career Doctrow was the Vice President of Promotional Marketing at Chiat/Day Inc. Advertising. During his time there, he helped to create multiple high-profile marketing campaigns for major brands that included Nike, Apple, Porsche, Mitsubishi Electric and Foster Farms. Doctrow also acted as Director of Promotions at Young & Rubicam, where he represented The 3M Company, Ralph's Supermarkets and the Harlem Globetrotters, among numerous prestigious clientele. 
Doctrow's career began at the United Artists Corporation where he developed promotions for UA and MGM titles across the Western United States.
